ot. Hes getting really really frustrating seeing that we did it the first 2 times with no problems at all and now the little Punk depops on us before he gets to the Dragon, Any Suggestions before my computer goes out my 3rd story window <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=295580"><br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.rinnie.hpg.com.br/sigs/kiros.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Click the pic to see my stuffs</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=radhaz>radhaz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.spiritpack.org/images/sigs/grrr.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 123<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/03 1:45 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.cox.net/radhazzone/images/barshhead.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoI Dragon - Xanamech Nexmirthafen </span><hr size=1> What method are you using to get your gnome to the dragon?  The standard chanter mez memblur method is how we've done it but also clear out the path pretty fast so theres not a whole lot of mezzing going on.  Regardlesss, I've read somewhere that he has a fairly short spawn time once triggered and its possible you are simply reaching that despawn point.  <br>
<br>
I know last sunday we took him to the dragon with no problems so I'm guessing he's not bugged (of course there's been two patches since then)<br>
<br>
Good luck bud <p><p align="center"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=115897" target="_blank"><img border="0" src="http://members.cox.net/radhazzone/images/sig/barsh_sig.gif" width="324" height="175"></a></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pilerboy>pilerboy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/03 2:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoI Dragon - Xanamech Nexmirthafen </span><hr size=1> Keep people out of his way... if he starts moving and someone is in front of him, he will keep walking into them, and then depop within 3 seconds.  that is your problem. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=193009"> Grendon's Stuff </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Member of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.familjen.dk">  Familjen </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Bristlebane Server<br>
<br>
&quot;Who ever heard of a hafling overlord, anyway?&quot;<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vikoz>Vikoz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/9/03 7:17 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoI Dragon - Xanamech Nexmirthafen </span><hr size=1> What pilerboy said. If peopel block his path, he will warp to his original spot, then depop. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://darksphereguild.com/Misc/vikoz.JPG"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=220745">My Gear</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> | <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Overlord of Darksphere</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> | <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://darksphereguild.com">My Guild</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jaqyl>Jaqyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/4/03 5:31 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.triad.rr.com/nexuscore/eqprofiles/Jaqezicon.jpg  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoI Dragon - Xanamech Nexmirthafen </span><hr size=1> Actually, the gnome doesn't depop, he gets killed.  When he warps back to his spawnpoint, he just starts on his path again, but since mobs have now repoped in the way, they slaughter him. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.triad.rr.com/nexuscore/eqprofiles/Jaqsig.jpg" style="border:0;"alt="Kezz is still a gimp!"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=63160" target="_blank">Jaqyl's Magelo</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> / <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=68040" target="_blank">Faustis's Magelo</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.orderofdraconis.com" target="_blank"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">Order of Draconis</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=farlanderb>FarlanderB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 98<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/8/03 1:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoI Dragon - Xanamech Nexmirthafen </span><hr size=1> He does have a despawn time. If he's left mezzed or rooted too long he will despawn. But yes, if he runs into someone, he does warp back to his spawn point and gets killed trying to path to the dragon.<br>
<br>
My guild just killed the dragon today with about 20 people. Now for our level of raiding, we consider this a tremendous achievement. Everything went smoothly. I died quickly, so did the secondary tank, but the third warrior (with about the same hitpoints but level 63) obtained aggro and tanked it to the end. I walked away with that nice hammer (13/19 effect: taunting blow, lots of stats).<br>
<br>
My question: Does anyone have any tips on keeping the gnome alive? We made sure the gnome had back the entire time, but we're afraid that he took a riposte or two during the fight and died. Is it possible to pull the gnome or the dragon away from one another and root the gnome? Or will this disrupt the quest? Thanks =) <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=607776">Veteran Farlander</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - 65 <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior">Overlord</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Fainel - 38 <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm">Enchanter</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.guild-legerdemain.com">Legerdemain</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> on <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/bprexus81531">Prexus</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raunstoncutter>RaunStoncutter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 351<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/9/03 8:24 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/raunstonecutter/bunnyhop.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoI Dragon - Xanamech Nexmirthafen </span><hr size=1> Everytime we do it, we have a bard and chanter on gnome control.  We've never had him do anything wierd like depop.  Usually we keep him moving though, if we need to hang tight, we only let him move a few feet, if we're on the run, we just let him go, since most of our raid has moved a good deal ahead of him.<br>
<br>
I guess just keep your raids pace fast, and know where to go. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=31658">Raun Stonecutter</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.swordoffate.com">&lt;Sword of Fate&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=124485">Deterious</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.swordoffate.com">&lt;Sword of Fate&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daxos92>Daxos92</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 145<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/9/03 8:52 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoI Dragon - Xanamech Nexmirthafen </span><hr size=1> Walking the gnome takes some getting used to, but the main thing is just to get the heck out of his way <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I don't think we've ever had Nitram get killed by the dragon before, we generally keep him to the side or back of the dragon by the MT's positioning. We've had a couple mishaps where someone on our raid will aggro the gnome mid-fight, which will bug the gnome and he won't give out any flags if you don't take care of that fast by the time the dragon dies (either by a blur or some other type of mem wipe, or just let the person who aggroed the gnome die).<br>
<br>
On one occasion, one of our rangers didn't catch that the gnome was in the line of his archery and slaughtered the little guy hehe. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=peligrostormseeker>Peligro Stormseeker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/9/03 9:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoI Dragon - Xanamech Nexmirthafen </span><hr size=1> Why dont you just have a monk holding aggro on the monk and then fd'ing?  thats the safest way I have seen.. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=9507" target="top">Peligro Stormseeker</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">.:. 65th season sexy Warrior serving Norrath the way a Overlord should .:. Proud Member of Lost Asylum</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fvighlander>Fvighlander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/9/03 5:28 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoI Dragon - Xanamech Nexmirthafen </span><hr size=1> FD isn't really a reliable mem wipe. I wouldn't choose a monk for that job anyway. We do use a tactic of having someone &quot;babysit&quot; the gnome, but it is a casting class who can generate aggro on the gnome without snaring or damaging him. When we're ready to move on, chanter mem blurs and off we go again. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=573077" target="_blank">Fvighlander</a><br>
Overlord of <a href="http://www.final-destiny.org" target="_blank">Final Destiny</a><br>
